Chaldaeos, magos, ‘ astrologers and magicians ². The raetice of consulting astrologers was common in the early Empire ἐξ. Hor. Od. i 113 ii 17, &c.). Augustus and Tiberius both patronized astrologers, and the latter was himself a student of their science (vi 20). In 16 A.D. astrologers were expelled from Italy by a decree of the senate (ii 32, 5), and two were actually executed ς and a similar order of expulsion was made in 52 Α. D. (xii 52, 3).
